{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Bring back access to luxury vehicles on Motability for disabled people",
        "additional_details": "I believe that if people who are capable of working are able to make enough money to buy luxury cars, then it is fair for Motability to allow disabled people to buy luxury cars. Motability customers still had to pay a large deposit for those cars so it\u2019s not as though they were getting them for free. And the only reason they\u2019re unable to work and earn the money to purchase these kind of cars themselves is because of restrictions due to their disability.",
        "background": "I\u2019d like the Government to allow Motability customers to access luxury vehicles just as a person who can work can.",
